Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the capacity-achieving property of polar codes, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper compares the performance of two decoding algorithms and discusses their computational complexity. 
3. cs.SI (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the error performance of a specific decoding algorithm for a communication system. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of a decoding algorithm for a communication system, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the performance of two decoding algorithms and their implementation, which is relevant to data structures and algorithms.
